projects.title: Irish Quaternary Association
projects.description:
Web Development - cpanel, php, css, html, web-hosting, domain-migration, wordpress

IQUA wanted a new website using WordPress that would be easy for the committee to update and that would feature a section on the front page showing their Facebook posts.

Built a customized WordPress theme and migrated it to their existing domain
Added tables to display their publications in a more user-friendly way 
Unlike the old site this is now responsive.
My goal in the site was to make it easier for a visitor to understand what the organization is and how to navigate the site (the old site involved so much clicking around through pages in search of information).

projects.title: The Hatchery
projects.description:
Web Development - responsive-web-design, web-hosting, php, javascript, css, html

The Hatchery wanted a WordPress site to showcase their new organization, all they had to give me was a powerpoint presentation. I took the content and style and developed a customized WordPress site.
Since the creation of the site they have raised funding to become a full 501c3 organization and are helping people advance their careers in the Chicago restaurant industry.
